COURSE: Business Mathematics I (BBA 1103)
WEEK: 16 of 16
DATE: March 2026

------------------------------------------------------------------------
LEARNING OBJECTIVES
------------------------------------------------------------------------
By the end of this week, students should be able to:

1. Understand fundamental mathematical concepts for business
2. Apply quantitative methods to business problems
3. Analyze data using statistical techniques
4. Interpret mathematical results in business context

------------------------------------------------------------------------
KEY TOPICS
------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Introduction to business mathematics principles
- Mathematical notation and terminology
- Problem-solving strategies
- Practical applications in business

